author: JJ Nattrass
title: 'Lock your door, Amy!': Kadeena Cox 'shoots death-stare' at model Willerton after epic crash - and Twitter goes wild
text:
Get celebs   Thank you for subscribing!   
She'd fought back from the brink in the first elimination round of Sunday's The Jump live final. 
However, Kadeena Cox crashed out moments after she was saved, after she was cut up in the ski cross event by Amy Willerton. 
And while the model, 24, was all smiles as she progressed to the final round, the 26-year-old Paralympian appeared to suffer a momentary lapse of grace as she seemingly shot a death-stare at Amy - and viewers were quick to pick up on it. Read More The Jump's Lydia Bright shares heartache at fellow TOWIE star James Argent's stint in rehab Are you feeling OK Kadeena? (Photo: Channel 4) 
With Spencer Matthews flying out ahead in the lead, closely followed by Kadeena, the gold medalist looked to be an easy second - and therefore safe for the final. 
Rocketing down the slope, desperate to catch her, Amy went neck and neck with the sporting hero before cutting her up and sending the two tumbling. 
And as Amy slid over the line first, Kadeena couldn't help but throw a thunderous stare her way as host Davina McCall interviewed her. Fans accused the Paralympian of being a sore loser after Amy Willerton crashed into her during the final (Photo: Channel 4) 
Spluttering that amy had "cut her up" as a nasty tactic, Davina was quick to tell her Amy had to cross in front of her to make it over the finish line. 
And, it would seem that viewers of the show were left unimpressed with Kadeena's attitude following the race. 
"She may be a gold medal paralympian but I'd award Kadeena Cox a Platinum medal in the sore loser stakes. Lock your door tonight Amy," tweeted one fan. 
Another avid The Jump fan, @connolly_fi, wrote: "Wow! Kadeena Cox having a sulk on #TheJumpC4 - it's only a game and I'm afraid you lost!" 
And plenty of other agreed too, with @geeee96 opining: "Kadeena Cox "she kinda cut me up" NO LOVE YOU LOST #TheJump2017 Well done @amywillerton ." 
While @blue_windmill quipped: "Poor sportsmanship from Kadeena Cox - she could learn something from my 3 year old about being gracious in defeat! #TheJump2017 ." 
Kadeena and Amy's epic crash came to nothing in the end, as once-again Amy became unbalanced later on in this show - resulting in her literally crashing out of the final round. 
Leaving it between Spencer Matthews and Louis Smith, former Made In Chelsea star Spencer managed to clinch an epic and unexpected win over Kadeena's fellow Team GB member. Like us on Facebook
